subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
With respect to external features, 

Phagocata pyrenaica

can be distinguished from its congeners by its dorsal pigmentation, which is dark brown or absent, depending on the population. The species also differs from its congeners in the following anatomical features: (
1
) in the proximity of the penis bulb, the vasa deferentia recurve vertically and dorsally, then descend again towards the penis bulb; (
2
) the ejaculatory duct runs along the ventral wall of the penis papilla; (
3
) the ejaculatory duct receives the opening of the penis glands, which is most probably erythrophilic, in its distal section.
